Based on the very good reviews we decided to give it a try. We went in a road trip which had 3 stops before reaching this accomodation. All the accomodations were booked through Airbnb and we found them to be great. Unfortunately, we cannot say the same thing about this one. In the previous reviews it was mentioned that the apartment was sparking clean. We would rather say that it was decent as the building is old and everything inside looks rather in need of restauration. The communication between us was rather difficult. As my boyfriend speaks fluently French we kept the communication in French to make it as smooth as possible for her. However, she misunderstood a question for information as an exact arrival time. Instead of confirming with us she got angry for not being there at that time. Even after we confirmed our real time of arrival she kept making us feel bad by sending us vague and confusing messages and, therefore, we changed our plans again (and therefore missing a part of our itinerary) to reach her apartment faster and not let her wait for us any longer. When we reached the place we found out that she is also living there so all the messages with "I am waiting at your place"; "I live nearby" did not make sense. I will not go more in detail, but it was bad enough to make us write our first negative feedback for an accomodation. Other information that might be valuable for you if you are still considering renting this room:
- we did not have any keys (we could get inside just if we arrived when she was at home which limited us for a nightly visit of Paris) and the bedroom doesn't lock;
- the bathroom is very small and you would share it with all the people that are staying in the apartment;
- the parking spot is in private alley that is situated behind the flat (even if she will tell you that it is right in front of the building). We had to find an available parking spot that was far away from her apartment and then she told us that we could have parked behind at number 168.

Sehr angenehmer Aufenthalt! Alles hat bestens geklappt. Richard hat mich empfangen obwohl ich etwas Verspätung hatte. Das Zimmer ist gut ausgestattet und sauber. Es liegt max. 20/25 Minuten vom Zentrum entfernt und liegt damit für Pariser Verhältnisse günstig.

